    for column_name in df.select_dtypes(include='object').columns:
            print(f'unique values in col "{column_name}": {df[column_name].unique()}')

def dist_density_charts(df):

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 8))

    row = 0

    for column in df.drop(['begin_date', 'end_date', 'senior_citizen', 'quit'], axis=1).select_dtypes(exclude='object'):

        sns.kdeplot(data=df, x=column, hue='quit', ax=ax[row, 0], multiple='stack', alpha=0.2)

        ax[row, 0].set_title(f"{column}_distribution_density_by_target_chart")

        ax[row, 0].axvline(df.query('quit == 1')[column].median(), color='orange', linestyle='--')
        ax[row, 0].axvline(df.query('quit == 0')[column].median(), color='dodgerblue', linestyle='--')

        ax[row, 0].legend(labels=[f"; : {round(df.query('quit == 1')[column].mean(), 2)}",
                                  f"; : {round(df.query('quit == 0')[column].mean(), 2)}"
                                 ]
                         )

        ax[row, 1].boxplot(df[column], vert=False)
        ax[row, 1].set_title(f"{column}_boxplot")
        ax[row, 1].set_xlabel(column)

        ax[row, 1].grid()

        row += 1

    fig.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def date_charts(df):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(20, 5))

    sns.histplot(data=df, x='begin_date', hue='quit', ax=ax[0], multiple='stack', alpha=0.2)

    ax[0].set_title(f"begin_date_histplot_by_target")

    ax[0].axvline(df.query('quit == 1')['begin_date'].median(), color='orange', linestyle='--')
    ax[0].axvline(df.query('quit == 0')['begin_date'].median(), color='dodgerblue', linestyle='--')

    ax[0].legend(labels=[f"; : {df.query('quit == 1')['begin_date'].median()}",
                         f"; : {df.query('quit == 0')['begin_date'].median()}"
                        ]
                )

    sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='total_charges', y='begin_date', hue='quit', ax=ax[1], alpha=0.6)

    ax[1].set_title(f"total_charges_begin_date_scatterplot_by_target")

    a = ax[1].axhline(df.query('quit == 1')['begin_date'].median(), color='orange', linestyle='--')
    b = ax[1].axhline(df.query('quit == 0')['begin_date'].median(), color='dodgerblue', linestyle='--')

    ax[1].legend(labels=[f"; : {df.query('quit == 1')['begin_date'].median()}",
                         f"; : {df.query('quit == 0')['begin_date'].median()}"
                        ],
                 handles = [a, b]
                )

    sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='monthly_charges', y='begin_date', hue='quit', ax=ax[2], alpha=0.6)

    ax[2].set_title(f"monthly_charges_begin_date_scatterplot_by_target")

    a = ax[2].axhline(df.query('quit == 1')['begin_date'].median(), color='orange', linestyle='--')
    b = ax[2].axhline(df.query('quit == 0')['begin_date'].median(), color='dodgerblue', linestyle='--')

    ax[2].legend(labels=[f"; : {df.query('quit == 1')['begin_date'].median()}",
                         f"; : {df.query('quit == 0')['begin_date'].median()}"
                        ],
                 handles = [a, b]
                )

    fig.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def duration_charts(df):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(20, 5))

    a = 0
    b = 1

    sns.histplot(data=df, x='duration_days', hue='quit', ax=ax[0], multiple='stack', legend='full', alpha=0.2)

    ax[0].set_title("duration_days_histplot_by_target")
    ax[0].legend(labels=['', ''])

    sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='total_charges', y='duration_days', hue='quit', ax=ax[1], legend='full', style='quit', size='quit', sizes=(50, 20), alpha=0.6)

    ax[1].set_title("total_charges_duration_scatterplot_by_target")
    h,l = ax[1].get_legend_handles_labels()
    ax[1].legend(handles=h, labels=['', ''])

    sns.scatterplot(data=df, x='monthly_charges', y='duration_days', hue='quit', ax=ax[2], legend='full', style='quit', size='quit', sizes=(50, 20), alpha=0.6)

    ax[2].set_title("monthly_charges_duration_scatterplot_by_target")
    h,l = ax[2].get_legend_handles_labels()
    ax[2].legend(handles=h, labels=['', ''])


    fig.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def bar_plotter(df):
    
    data = df.copy()
    data['senior_citizen'] = data['senior_citizen'].astype('object')
    
    drop_cols = ['customer_id', 'end_date']
    
    quitters = data.query('quit == 1')
    remainers = data.query('quit == 0')

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(5, 3, figsize=(15, 25))

    row = 0
    col = 0
    
    for column in data.drop(drop_cols, axis=1).select_dtypes(include='object'):

        info = pd.DataFrame(data.pivot_table(values=['quit'], columns=[column], aggfunc='value_counts'))

        ax[row, col] = sns.barplot(data=info, x=column, y='count', hue='quit', ax=ax[row, col])
        
        ax[row, col].bar_label(ax[row, col].containers[0], fontsize=10)
        ax[row, col].bar_label(ax[row, col].containers[1], fontsize=10)

        h,l = ax[row, col].get_legend_handles_labels()
        ax[row, col].legend(handles=h, labels=['', ''])
        
        ax[row, col].set_title('{}_chart'.format(column))
        
        ax[row, col].xaxis.label.set_visible(False)
        
        ax[row, col].grid(axis='y')
        
        plt.setp(ax[row, col].get_xticklabels(), rotation=-15, ha="left", rotation_mode="anchor")
        
        if col < 2:
            col += 1
        else:
            row += 1
            col = 0
            
    
    fig.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
In[7]:
def recall_threshold_table(model, X_test, y_test, linspace_start=0, linspace_end=1, linspace_num=5):
    
    y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
    
    data = pd.DataFrame(zip(y_test, y_proba),
                        columns=['y_valid', 'y_proba']).sort_values(by='y_proba', ascending=False)
    
    thresholds = [round(i, 2) for i in np.linspace(linspace_start, linspace_end, num=linspace_num, endpoint=False)]
    
    columns = []
    
    for i in thresholds:
        columns.append('y_pred_' + str(i))
        data['y_pred_' + str(i)] = data['y_proba'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x >= i else 0)
    
    recall_list = []
    predicted_objects = []
    all_objects_class_1 = data.loc[data['y_valid'] == 1, 'y_valid'].count()
    
    for column in data.drop(['y_valid', 'y_proba'], axis=1).columns:
        recall_list.append(round(recall_score(data['y_valid'], data[column]), 2))
        predicted_objects.append(data.loc[(data[column] == 1) & (data['y_valid'] == 1)][column].count())
    
    recall_thresholds = {'': data.drop(['y_valid', 'y_proba'], axis=1).columns,
                         'recall': recall_list,
                         '   ': predicted_objects,
                         '   1': all_objects_class_1
                        }
    
    rt_info = pd.DataFrame(recall_thresholds)
    
    return rt_info

num_cols = ['total_charges', 'monthly_charges', 'duration_days']
cat_cols = X.drop(num_cols + ['senior_citizen'], axis=1).columns.to_list()

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=RANDOM_STATE, stratify=y)

encoder = OrdinalEncoder(handle_unknown='use_encoded_value',
                         encoded_missing_value=-1,
                         unknown_value=np.nan
                        )

train_encoded = pd.DataFrame(encoder.fit_transform(X_train[cat_cols]),
                             columns=encoder.get_feature_names_out(), index=X_train.index
                            )
test_encoded = pd.DataFrame(encoder.transform(X_test[cat_cols]),
                            columns=encoder.get_feature_names_out(), index=X_test.index
                           )

X_train = pd.concat([X_train[num_cols], train_encoded], axis=1)
X_test = pd.concat([X_test[num_cols], test_encoded], axis=1)

def get_train_tpr_fpr(cv):
    pred_proba = cv.best_estimator_.predict_proba(X_train)[:, 1]
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_train, pred_proba)
    return fpr, tpr
    
tree_fpr, tree_tpr = get_train_tpr_fpr(rscv_tree)
forest_fpr, forest_tpr = get_train_tpr_fpr(rscv_forest)
lgb_fpr, lgb_tpr = get_train_tpr_fpr(grid_lgb)
cb_fpr, cb_tpr = get_train_tpr_fpr(grid_cb)
dummy_fpr, dummy_cpr = get_train_tpr_fpr(dummy_clf_grid)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(14, 7))

tree = ax.plot(tree_fpr, tree_tpr, linestyle='-', linewidth=1.7, label='tree')
forest = ax.plot(forest_fpr, forest_tpr, linestyle=':', linewidth=1.7, label='forest')
lgb = ax.plot(lgb_fpr, lgb_tpr, linestyle='-.', linewidth=1.7, label='lgb')
cb = ax.plot(cb_fpr, cb_tpr, linestyle='--', linewidth=1.7, label='cb')
dummy = ax.plot(dummy_fpr, dummy_cpr, linestyle='-', linewidth=1.7, label='dummy')

lns = tree+forest+lgb+cb+dummy

In[56]:
def prob_by_threshold(model, X_test, y_test, threshold=0.5):
    y_proba = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]
    data = pd.DataFrame(zip(y_test, y_proba), columns=['y_valid', 'y_proba']).sort_values(by='y_proba', ascending=True)
    
    data['y_pred_' + str(threshold)] = data['y_proba'].apply(lambda x: 1 if x >= threshold else 0)
    
    return data

threshold_data_0_01 = prob_by_threshold(grid_cb.best_estimator_, X_test, y_test, 0.01)
threshold_data_01 = prob_by_threshold(grid_cb.best_estimator_, X_test, y_test, 0.1)

ax[0].set_ylabel('True label')
ax[0].set_xlabel('Predicted')
ax[0].set_title('threshold=0.01')

cm2 = confusion_matrix(threshold_data_01['y_valid'], threshold_data_01['y_pred_0.1'])
sns.heatmap(cm2, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues_r', ax=ax[1])

ax[1].set_ylabel('True label')
